      <section eId="sec_250">
        <num>250</num>
        <heading>Agreements relating to marriage; statute of limitations</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_250__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>prior to a marriage or</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_250__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>during the marriage,\nbut prior to the service of process in a matrimonial action or\nproceeding, shall be three years.\n  2. The statute of limitations shall be tolled until</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_250__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>process has\nbeen served in such matrimonial action or proceeding, or</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_250__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the death\nof one of the parties.\n  3. The provisions of this section shall not apply to a separation\nagreement or an agreement made during the pendency of a matrimonial\naction or in settlement thereof.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
